---
description: Use markdown content collections for site data and handle empty states.
alwaysApply: true
---

# Content Delivery Rule

- Store user-facing content as markdown in `src/content/**` rather than hardcoding in Astro/TS.
- Keep content in topic folders (e.g., `src/content/activities/events/`, `src/content/blog/`).
- Load content with `getCollection()` and group/sort by frontmatter fields.
- Always handle empty states and missing optional fields gracefully.

## Example

```astro
---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
const items = await getCollection('activities');
const events = items.filter((item) => item.data.category === 'events');
---
{events.length ? events.map((item) => <p>{item.data.title}</p>) : <p>No events yet.</p>}
```
